bib_record.title: Capture Cross Section Measurements for Lu, 151Eu, and 153Eu and Total Cross Section of Eu*

free_txt: Original compiler's comment: "Do not use data. Detector
found to be picking up extraneous signals." Could not
find the reason for this statement.
Moxon-Rae detectors placed 11.59 cm
from the center of each sample. The detectors had
Bi203+C radiators 7.6x8x0.95 cm thick and totally
depleted (300 micron) , diffused junction, solid state
detectors for the detection of the conversion
electrons. 6LiF foils, silicon detector.
Underground nuclear explosion.
The flight path between beam monitor labeled
6Li and the neutron source, a low yield nuclear
device, was 307.2 m. The neutron beam that resulted
from the detonation of this device was collimated by
a circular aperture, located below ground level, of
such a diameter that the beam was 4.0 cm diameter at
the monitor 6Li. Neutron energy was determined from
the known flight path and the measured time of
arrival of the neutrons at a particular target.
Source neutrons were moderated by polyethylene.
Neutron monitor.
Relative errors in these cross sections
are at least 8%.
Natural Lu: 1.61x10**-3 atom/barn. Samples were
elliptically shaped with a minor axis of 5.1 cm and a
major axis of 7.2 cm, were orientated 45 degree to
the beam, and were centered on the beam axis. All
samples were self supporting metallic foils.
Fig. 4, page 844.
Relative errors in these cross sections
are at least 8%.
Density was 1.43*10**-3
atom/barn. Samples were elliptically shaped with a
minor axis of 5.1 cm and a major axis of 7.2 cm, were
orientated 45 degree to the beam, and were centered
on the beam axis. All samples were self supporting
metallic foils. The europium foils were coated on
both sides with 945 microg/cm2 of Al to retard
oxidation and subsequent deterioration. These foils
were made by the Isotopes Division of Oak Ridge
National Laboratory.
Fig. 2, page 843.
Relative errors in these cross sections

Fig. 3, page 843.
These data are not a result of a separate measurement
but were calculated from the transmission in the
other measurements.
Corrections to these total cross sections for
in-scattering effects, aluminum deposits on the
samples, and the nickel backings of the 6LiF foils
were found to be negligible.
The relative error of at least 21 barns
restricts the useful energy range to 25-1500 eV.
Mixture of two isotopes.
Fig. 5, page 844.
